[*]
xpl_openrelay: [ref]: MAPS\nAn Internet mail server performs third-party relay when it processes a\nmessage from a non-local sender to a non-local recipient. These days,\njunk emailers abuse this capability at an alarming rate. They use the\nstolen capacity to greatly increase the amount of spam they can deliver.\n[adv]: AFNIC\nYou can perform more complete testing by using the following command:\n"telnet relay-test.mail-abuse.org", for more information take a look at\n<URL:http://www.mail-abuse.org/>



[chk_mail_openrelay_domain]
testname: delegated domain is not an openrelay
error   : The best MX for the domain is an openrelay
ok	: The best MX for the domain doesn't seem to be an openrelay
explain = xpl_openrelay
details : The mailhost (%{mailhost}) used for receiving email for your domain seems to act as an open relay, it is allowing mail from %{from_host} to %{to_host}.


[chk_mail_openrelay_hostmaster]
testname: domain of the hostmaster email is not an openrelay
error   : The best MX for the hostmaster address is an openrelay
ok	: The best MX for the hostmaster address doesn't seem to be an openrelay
explain = xpl_openrelay
details : The mailhost (%{mailhost}) used for the hostmaster address (%{hostmaster}) seems to act as an open relay, it is allowing mail from %{from_host} to %{to_host}.


[chk_mail_delivery_postmaster]
testname: can deliver email to 'postmaster'
error   : The postmaster can't be contacted by email
ok	: The postmaster can be contacted by email
explain : [ref]: IETF RFC1123 (p.51  5.2.7  RCPT Command: RFC-821 Section 4.1.1)\nA host that supports a receiver-SMTP MUST support the reserved\nmailbox "Postmaster".
details : Unable to send email to the postmaster address (%{postmaster}).


[chk_mail_delivery_hostmaster]
testname: can deliver email to hostmaster
error   : The hostmaster can't be contacted by email
ok	: The hostmaster can be contacted by email
explain : [none]
details : Unable to send email to the hostmaster address (%{hostmaster}).


[chk_mail_hostmaster_mx_cname]
testname: hostmaster MX is not an alias
error   : The hostmaster MX is not allow to point to a CNAME alias
ok	: The hostmaster MX is not an alias
explain : [ref]: IETF RFC974\nMX records shall not point to an alias defined by a CNAME.

[chk_mail_mx_or_addr]
testname: domain able to receive email (delivery using MX, A, AAAA)
error   : The domain doesn't have an MX or an address for mail delivery
ok      : The domain is able to receive email
explain	: [none]


